---
// Terms of Service · Approved by Danish (CLO), 28 April 2026
// Calibrated to: Tamazia's actual delivery model (consultative engagements + monthly retainers)
// across UK, EU, US, GCC, Singapore, Hong Kong jurisdictions.
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/layout/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/layout/Footer.astro';
const lastUpdated = '28 April 2026';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service · Tamazia"
  description="Terms governing use of tamazia.in and engagement with Tamazia. Read alongside the privacy notice and cookie policy."
>
  <Header />
  <main id="main" class="legal-page">
    <article class="legal-inner">
      <p class="eyebrow">Legal · Terms</p>
      <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Last updated: {lastUpdated}. These terms govern your use of tamazia.in and any preliminary
        engagement with Tamazia preceding a signed Statement of Work. Formal client engagements are
        governed by the executed engagement letter, which prevails over these terms in case of conflict.
      </p>

      <section>
        <h2>1. Who we are</h2>
        <p>
          Tamazia is an international SEO and regulatory-compliance content firm. Founder and principal:
          Aman Pareek, LLM in International Business Law (King's College London). The firm operates
          cross-jurisdictionally with delivery in the United Kingdom, European Union, United States, GCC
          (UAE, Saudi Arabia, Qatar, Bahrain), Singapore, and Hong Kong.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>2. Use of this website</h2>
        <p>You may use tamazia.in for personal, business, or research purposes provided you:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Do not attempt to disrupt, scan, or stress-test the infrastructure.</li>
          <li>Do not scrape content for republication without written permission.</li>
          <li>Do not submit false or misleading information through any form.</li>
          <li>Comply with applicable laws of the jurisdiction from which you access the site.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>3. Submissions and enquiries</h2>
        <p>
          Information you submit through forms on this site (Quick Audit, briefing request, regulatory
          briefings signup) is processed under our <a href="/privacy">privacy notice</a>. Submitting an
          enquiry does not create a client relationship. A client relationship is created only by
          signed engagement letter or Statement of Work executed by Tamazia.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>4. Audit output and recommendations</h2>
        <p>
          Audit outputs delivered through this site (whether free, sample, or paid) are professional
          opinions based on the data available at the time of analysis. They are not legal advice and
          are not a substitute for guidance from your retained counsel or compliance team. Tamazia may
          reference regulatory frameworks such as UK GDPR, EU GDPR, HIPAA, SEC Reg FD, MiFID II, ICC
          Rules, LCIA Rules, SRA Standards, FDA Title 21, and others. Each reference reflects
          publicly available regulator text current at the time of audit; regulator interpretations
          evolve and should be verified before action.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>5. Intellectual property</h2>
        <p>
          All content on tamazia.in — copy, design, code, brand marks — is the intellectual property of
          Tamazia or its licensors. Audit reports and deliverables produced for paying clients are
          governed by the licence terms in the executed engagement letter.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>6. Confidentiality</h2>
        <p>
          Information you share in support of a paid engagement is treated as confidential and processed
          only for the purpose of that engagement. Standard professional-confidentiality obligations
          apply. We are happy to execute a mutual non-disclosure agreement before sensitive disclosures.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>7. Third-party services and links</h2>
        <p>
          Insights articles and audit outputs may reference third-party regulators, publications, or
          tools. Such references do not constitute endorsement. Tamazia is not responsible for the
          content of external sites linked from this domain.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>8. Liability</h2>
        <p>
          tamazia.in is provided "as is" for informational purposes. To the maximum extent permitted by
          applicable law, Tamazia is not liable for any indirect, incidental, consequential, or
          exemplary damages arising from use of this website or reliance on its content. Liability for
          paid engagements is governed by the engagement letter and its express limitation-of-liability
          clauses.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>9. Governing law and disputes</h2>
        <p>
          These website terms are governed by the laws of England and Wales. Disputes arising from use
          of this website are subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of England and Wales.
          For disputes arising under a paid engagement, the governing-law and dispute-resolution clauses
          of the executed engagement letter prevail (typically arbitration under ICC, LCIA, SIAC, or
          DIAC Rules depending on the engagement).
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>10. Changes</h2>
        <p>
          Material changes to these terms are versioned by the "Last updated" date at the top. Continued
          use of tamazia.in after a change constitutes acceptance of the revised terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>11. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions about these terms: <a href="mailto:realfamemedia@gmail.com">realfamemedia@gmail.com</a>.
          For data-subject requests under UK GDPR / EU GDPR / UAE PDPL, see the
          <a href="/privacy">privacy notice</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <p class="legal-footer-note">
        Read alongside the <a href="/privacy">privacy notice</a> and <a href="/cookie-policy">cookie
        policy</a>. Engagement letters and Statements of Work govern paid relationships.
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-page { background: var(--ivory); color: var(--oxblood-ink); padding: 80px 0 120px; }
  .legal-inner { max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px; font-family: var(--ff-body, Inter, system-ui, sans-serif); }
  .eyebrow { font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.24em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--gold-text-strong, #5C3F18); margin: 0 0 16px; }
  h1 { font-family: var(--ff-display, 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif); font-size: clamp(36px, 5vw, 52px); font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.15; margin: 0 0 24px; color: var(--oxblood); }
  .lede { font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--oxblood-wine); margin: 0 0 48px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gold); padding-bottom: 32px; }
  section { margin: 0 0 40px; }
  h2 { font-family: var(--ff-display, 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif); font-size: clamp(20px, 2.4vw, 26px); font-weight: 500; margin: 0 0 16px; color: var(--oxblood-ink); }
  p, li { font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; margin: 0 0 14px; color: var(--oxblood-wine); }
  ul { padding-left: 22px; margin: 0 0 14px; }
  a { color: var(--gold-text-strong, #5C3F18); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 3px; }
  a:hover { color: var(--oxblood); }
  .legal-footer-note { margin: 56px 0 0; padding: 24px 0 0; border-top: 1px solid rgba(201, 167, 114, 0.4); font-size: 13px; font-style: italic; color: var(--oxblood-mist, #6D2037); }
  @media (max-width: 640px) { .legal-page { padding: 56px 0 80px; } .lede { font-size: 16px; padding-bottom: 24px; margin-bottom: 36px; } }
</style>
